Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.550 --> 00:00:03.710
So, when you're walking into a brick and
mortar store in the real world.

00:00:03.710 --> 00:00:06.170
It's pretty obvious that you're
going to put down some money and

00:00:06.170 --> 00:00:07.450
you're going to buy something.

00:00:07.450 --> 00:00:08.610
Is that similar for apps?

00:00:09.800 --> 00:00:10.630
&gt;&gt; Yes and no.

00:00:10.630 --> 00:00:13.320
If you wish to charge user
before they download your app,

00:00:13.320 --> 00:00:15.190
you can do it in a simple way.

00:00:15.190 --> 00:00:17.550
First, create a Merchant Account.

00:00:17.550 --> 00:00:21.520
Second, set the prices for
your app in the Developer Console.

00:00:21.520 --> 00:00:25.290
Third, you can optionally
include advertising or

00:00:25.290 --> 00:00:28.790
use In-app billing to sell
additional features or content.

00:00:28.790 --> 00:00:32.400
Web links to all the three stages
in the instructor notes down below.

00:00:33.490 --> 00:00:36.640
It's important to remember
who are you targeting?

00:00:36.640 --> 00:00:40.570
Since this model may limit your
app monetization potential.

00:00:40.570 --> 00:00:42.800
Particularly in developing market.

00:00:42.800 --> 00:00:46.330
You may be able to achieve greater
revenue by using the freemium or

00:00:46.330 --> 00:00:47.380
subscription models.

